DefaultMessage.SourceString:
What do you mean <b>"Other Joneses?" </>
Are they here?

Don't you <b>get it?</> 
There is no <b>Agent Jones!</>
That guy's just itching for an excuse to kick my -
JONES IS <b>DOOMED. </>

Right on, man. 
I always thought I'd be <b>a hero. </>
But if I know me, I probably don't want to be stuck in a <b>weird limbo between worlds. </>
Sometimes bits and pieces come back to me when I'm <b>on a dive. </>
I came here on a <b>mission to study the zero point...</>
It looks like Jones asked the <b>right person</> for help.
If you <b>really</> want to get wrapped up in this <b>maybe</> I'll help.
Prove to me you really want to learn what's going on here. Then <b>maybe</> we'll talk.
Do they have <b>food?</>

I was involved in <b>The Spire? </>
Looks like I'm never earning my <b>Cautious Camper Sash Badge.</>
According to the <b>IO Agent Field Guide,</> memory loss is a very common when entering <b>the loop. </>
Or...
Maybe we'll end this right here.
You want my help?

<b>Not bad. </>
Guess I underestimated you.
There are people who think <b>the Spire</> will make them <b>powerful.</>
Do not allow <b>the Spire</> to corrupt someone <enemy>powerful</>
It will, but it will also exploit their every <b>weakness. </>
or <b>Jones</> does not stand a chance.

Me? Working with <b>The Foundation?</>
Not likely.
I figured that out in the bunker.
You can <b>figure out</> a lot of stuff in a bunker.
Wait - how do <b>you</> know about the Foundation?
Also... how do <b>I</> know about The Foundation...
And most of us don't even know that we've forgotten... all the stuff we've forgotten.
Supposedly it gets worse the more times you enter the <b>loop. </>
Can't remember who told me that...
When you find a Jones who knows what's going on,

So I don't know if any of us can help you...
unless...
... the rumors of <b>The First Jones</> are true.
Me? Best I can guess is I was on some sort of <b>undercover mission. </>

That's all you're getting from me. 
I'm not losing my <b>No Snitching Badge. </>
Maybe one of the <b>other Joneses</> can help.
But once you're in the loop you're just an <b>echo of who you once were...</>
Well... that's true for <b>most</> of us....
Up to you.
Get ready to <enemy>fight!</>
HA HA HA HA HA!
ONLY <b>THE FIRST JONES</> COULD HELP NOW.
NOW <b>SLURP OFF!</>
Go now, before <b>the Spire</> attracts any more attention from the -
Never mind, just <b>hurry!</>
ask about my whole <b>dino situation,</> would ya?
<b>The Loop</> does strange things to your memory.
Doesn't matter. Once you're here, you're <b>here. </>

Once you're here, you're not <b>you. </>
You're like a <b>snapshot</> of who you were.

You needed a Jones and you came to me? 
<b>Look at me!</>

You know why I'm dressed like a dinosaur? 
Because I <b>sure don't. </>
